4508:/// The Apple Container daemon process is alive but its internal
4509:/// Virtualization.framework state is stale (e.g. after an interrupted
4510:/// macOS restart/sleep). Containers are created but immediately exit
4511:/// with `NSPOSIXErrorDomain Code=22 "Invalid argument"`.
4512:/// Restarting the daemon (`container system stop && container system start`)
4513:/// is the only fix — retrying will never help.
4514:fn is_apple_container_daemon_stale_error(text: &str) -> bool {
4515:    // Both patterns are required — `NSPOSIXErrorDomain` alone can appear in
4516:    // benign log-fetching errors (Code=2 "No such file or directory") when a
4517:    // container vanishes. The stale-daemon signature is specifically EINVAL:
4518:    // `NSPOSIXErrorDomain Code=22 "Invalid argument"`.
4519:    text.contains("NSPOSIXErrorDomain") && text.contains("Invalid argument")
4520:}
