4522:/// Returns `true` when a freshly created container stopped immediately and
4523:/// produced no meaningful logs. This indicates the VM never fully booted —
4524:/// a broader symptom than the specific daemon-stale EINVAL signature. It can
4525:/// occur after macOS sleep/wake cycles, resource exhaustion, or
4526:/// Virtualization.framework glitches. The appropriate recovery is a full
4527:/// service restart, same as for daemon-stale errors.
4528:#[cfg(any(target_os = "macos", test))]
4529:fn is_apple_container_boot_failure(logs: Option<&str>) -> bool {
4530:    match logs {
4531:        None => true,
4532:        Some(text) => {
4533:            let trimmed = text.trim();
4534:            if trimmed.is_empty() {
4535:                return true;
4536:            }
4537:            // Log-retrieval errors about a missing stdio.log mean
4538:            // the VM never produced any output.
4539:            trimmed.contains("stdio.log") && trimmed.contains("doesn't exist")
4540:        },
4541:    }
4542:}
