5296:/// Check whether an error message indicates a Podman runtime issue that warrants
5297:/// failover. Podman is daemonless so most Docker-daemon errors don't apply, but
5298:/// socket/service errors or missing runtimes do.
5299:fn is_podman_failover_error(message: &str) -> bool {
5300:    let lower = message.to_ascii_lowercase();
5301:    lower.contains("cannot connect to podman")
5302:        || lower.contains("no such file or directory") && lower.contains("podman")
5303:        || lower.contains("connection refused")
5304:        || lower.contains("runtime") && lower.contains("not found")
5305:}
